  "prompt": "Which roaming app offers the cheapest roaming rates?",
  "response": "The \"cheapest\" roaming app can vary based on your specific needs, such as your destination, data usage, and call/text requirements. However, as of 2023, here are a few popular apps known for competitive roaming rates:\n\n1. **Airalo**  \n   - Offers eSIMs for data-only roaming in over 190 countries.  \n   - Plans are affordable and flexible, with no hidden fees.  \n   - Ideal for travelers who only need data.\n\n2. **Flexiroam**  \n   - Provides affordable data roaming plans in over 150 countries.  \n   - Offers both physical SIM cards and eSIM options.  \n   - Often has promotions and discounts for new users.\n\n3. **KnowRoaming**  \n   - Offers global SIM cards and eSIMs with competitive rates for calls, texts, and data.  \n   - Great for frequent travelers who need voice and data.\n\n4. **TextNow** (for U.S. travelers)  \n   - Provides free texting and low-cost international calling.  \n   - Requires Wi-Fi or a data connection but can be a budget-friendly option for light users.\n\n5. **Dent Wireless**  \n   - Offers eSIMs for data roaming in over 60 countries.  \n   - Plans are pay-as-you-go, so you only pay for what you use.\n\n6. **Orange Holiday**  \n   - Offers physical SIM cards with generous data, call, and text allowances for Europe and beyond.  \n   - Often cheaper than traditional roaming plans from major carriers.\n\n### Tips for Choosing the Best App:  \n- **Check coverage:** Ensure the app covers your destination.  \n- **Compare plans:** Look at data allowances, call rates, and validity periods.  \n- **Read reviews:** User feedback can help you avoid hidden fees or poor service.  \n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, check the apps' official websites or compare plans on platforms like **SimOptions** or **PlanHub**.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
